Package: crasch
Type: Package
Title: Construct Mapping with Rasch
Version: 0000.0000.9000
Date: 2015-12-10
Author: c(person("Amy","Arneson",email="aea@berkeley.edu",role=c("aut","cre")),
    person("Rebecca","Freund",email="rlfreund@berkeley.edu",role="ctb"),
    person("Mark","Wilson",email="markw@berkeley.edu",role="ctb"))
Description: An organizational and analysis tool that faciliatates
    implemenation of the Berkeley Assessment System, following that of
    Wilson (2004). Provides user-friendly wrappers for Rasch model estimation
    (performed by either mirt or TAM). Produces nicely formatted and readable
    tables and graphics for those with little to no R-coding experience.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
LazyData: TRUE
Depends:
    WrightMap,
    RColorBrewer
Imports:
    mirt,
    lme4,
    sirt,
    Hmisc,
    boot,
    ltm
Suggests:
    TAM,
    testthat
RoxygenNote: 5.0.1
